Alisal Guest Ranch - Solvang

1054 Alisal Road, Solvang, California, 93463

​Phone: +1 (805) 688-6411

​A secluded and sprawling ranch in the scenic Santa Ynez Valley, with 50 miles of trails, two golf courses, tennis courts, a lake, pool, spa, and fine dining, Free Wifi, Free Parking, Breakfast included​

The Ritz-Carlton Bacara Santa Barbara

8301 Hollister Avenu. Santa Barbara, CA 93117

Phone: +1 (805) 968 0100

Located in Goleta, Santa Barbara, overlooking the Pacific, the The Ritz-Carlton Bacara, two restaurants, three pools, spa facilities, and a gym. On-site parking is also available.

LA PURISIMA MISSION STATE HISTORIC PARK 2295 Purisima Road , Lompoc , CA 93436

(805) 733-3713

http://www.lapurisimamission.org/

Founded in 1787, the La Purisima Mission land holdings once covered nearly 470 square miles. Bordered by the Santa Maria River in the North and the Gaviota coastline in the South, the land was home to the Chumash people and Spanish settlers. The mission was best known for its hides and blankets, and at its peak inhabitants herded as many as 24,000 cattle and sheep.

MURALS OF LOMPOC

Inspired by a trip to British Columbia, Gene and Judy Stevens started the murals over 30 years ago. Lompoc has close to 30 major commissioned murals in its inventory. They all depict a part of Lompoc’s history and are located primarily in the old downtown area.

You can see a map of all the murals here

LOMPOC MUSEUM

​ Established in 1969, the Lompoc Museum exhibits document the archeology and history of the Lompoc Valley and Santa Barbara County. The Museum was established in Lompoc’s former Carnegie Library to display the Clarence Ruth Collection of Chumash and other Native American artifacts.

More info: ​http://www.lompocmuseum.org/

​​ARTESIA SCHOOL MUSEUM

​The Artesia School Museum is a fully restored and furnished one-room country schoolhouse. Built in 1876, Artesia was the first country school in the Lompoc Valley. It remained in constant use until 1961. A City and County Landmark, Artesia is open to the public the fourth Saturday of every month from 2 - 4 pm. More info http://www.lompocmuseum.org/artesia.php

JALAMA BEACH COUNTY PARK

​9999 Jalama Road, Lompoc, CA 93436

Park Reservations (805) 568-2460

Hours: Monday - Friday, 9:00 am - 3:00 pm, except holidays. Online Reservations are available 24 hours, 365 days/year [email protected]

https://www.countyofsb.org/parks/jalama.sbc

Jalama ... the perfect place to surf, sunbathe or simply explore. Miles of sandy beach, waves breaking on the shore, and little sign of civilization.
